1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:13,200
2. You will hear the chairperson of the Middletown Urban Farming scheme talking to a group

2
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:16,920
of people who are interested in joining the scheme.

3
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:23,760
First, you have some time to look at questions 11-16 on page 3.

4
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:13,920
Now listen carefully and answer questions 11-16.

5
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:22,320
I'm Chris Butler, and I'm the chairperson of the Middletown Urban Farming scheme, or

6
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:28,120
MUFS for short, a highly successful program which encourages city dwellers to grow their

7
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:32,680
own fruit and vegetables to become city farmers if you will.

8
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:34,680
Who started MUFS?

9
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:40,360
Well, the idea of urban farming has been around for quite a while, particularly among town

10
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:42,040
planners.

11
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:47,040
But it was actually a group of Middletown business people, including myself, who decided

12
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:50,560
to create what became MUFS.

13
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:53,880
University agriculture specialists got involved later.

14
00:01:53,880 --> 00:02:00,440
Now, initially, the aim was not some eco-friendly goal of reducing CO2 emissions caused by the

15
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:03,880
transport of food from farm to dinner plate.

16
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:09,080
It was simply to maximize the utilization of the vacant or idle land that lies within

17
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:10,080
the city.

18
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:15,800
Of course, later we realized that an additional benefit might be a healthier diet for local

19
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:17,600
people.

20
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:21,080
Let me tell you a bit about the groups that have joined the scheme.

21
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:26,520
We've got any number of schools involved and loads of corporate employees, so our message

22
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:29,120
seems to have been well received there.

23
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:33,760
But for next year, we're going to concentrate on getting various community centers, like

24
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:39,080
those for senior citizens to join, because so far, they've been somewhat slow to take

25
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:40,520
up the scheme.

26
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:47,560
Now, the core committee of the MUFS is a group of dedicated gardeners.

27
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:51,680
They probably won't be familiar with your specific plot of land.

28
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:53,480
They're mostly amateurs.

29
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:58,320
But they are the people who know the ins and outs of gardening, and they will be happy

30
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:04,760
to sit down with any MUFS member and make some hands-on suggestions about gardening.

31
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:09,800
But don't expect them to know the answers to technical questions, like the Latin names

32
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:11,880
of plants.

33
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:17,160
The MUFS are keen to support members who are physically disabled.

34
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:21,400
They're looking at the possibility of providing specially adapted gardening tools on loan

35
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:24,880
to members who can't cope with regular tools.

36
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:26,560
That's not happening yet.

37
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:31,800
But we do have some window boxes, as well as larger containers, which we can distribute

38
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:36,280
free of charge to these members, although they will have to provide their own soil and

39
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:37,880
compost to themselves.

40
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:43,080
I'm especially proud of the work we've done with the local schools, both grade school

41
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:45,040
level and high schools.

42
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:49,640
The teachers say that they knew the scheme would be of some practical use in science classes

43
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:51,560
like biology.

44
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:56,440
Despite the original hopes of some, the fruit and vegetable plots haven't provided cheaper

45
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,720
lunches for their students.

46
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:03,720
But what they didn't anticipate was the change in attitude that the scheme has created

47
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:05,560
amongst their students.

48
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:10,000
They say the students have become much more conscious of their surrounding environment.

49
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:15,240
They want to keep it neat and tidy.

50
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:21,760
Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions 17-20 on

51
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,720
page 4.

52
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:50,840
Now listen and answer questions 17-20.

53
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:56,920
Now a number of local organizations and businesses provide our members with free goods and services.

54
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,680
Let me go through some of them.

55
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:04,840
The city hospital, as you might expect, has to provide thousands of meals for its patients.

56
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:10,040
Until the manager of its kitchen runs a course for our members on how to use vegetables

57
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:12,880
in a huge variety of dishes.

58
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:18,080
The local government found it had a large glass building, which the Parks Department used,

59
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:21,800
to start off flower seeds in young plants during the winter.

60
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:26,680
And they agreed to allow our members to use this free of charge to get their own little

61
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:29,800
seedlings off to a good start.

62
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:30,960
Another thing.

63
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:36,080
The university has agreed that if members send them a sample of their soil, they will

64
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:41,800
do a series of tests on it to indicate what kind of plants will grow best and what types

65
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:45,520
of fertilizer and nutrients would be best to use.

66
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:50,320
And just to make sure our members know what's good for them, a supermarket is offering a

67
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:56,200
series of classes on how to lose weight and stay healthy by having a sensible diet.

68
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:58,920
Now, let's talk about the practicalities.

69
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:05,800
That is the end of section 2.

70
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:09,000
You now have half a minute to check your answers.

71
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:42,520
Now turn to section 3 on page 5.

